<refnamediv><refname>imbwareaopen3</refname><refpurpose>Remove small connected objects from a 3-D binary volume.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imbwareaopen3(volume, minimumSize)
out = imbwareaopen3(volume, minimumSize, connectivity)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist>
<varlistentry><term>volume</term><listitem><para>Binary or numeric 3-D volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>minimumSize</term><listitem><para>Minimum component size in voxels.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>connectivity</term><listitem><para><literal>6</literal>, <literal>18</literal>, or <literal>26</literal>. Default is 26.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Boolean volume containing retained components.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Labels foreground components natively and removes every component containing fewer than <varname>minimumSize</varname> voxels.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
volume = zeros(35, 35, 18) == 1;
volume(8:25, 8:25, 5:14) = %t;
volume(3, 4, 2) = %t;
volume(31:32, 30:31, 16) = %t;
clean = imbwareaopen3(volume, 20, 26);
imshow3d(clean, "3d", 1, 7000);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
